====================================================================
TERRAFORM VARIABLES & VARIABLE FILES 
====================================================================

--------------------------------------------------
WHAT ARE TERRAFORM VARIABLES?
--------------------------------------------------

    Terraform variables are used to make infrastructure
    code reusable and flexible.

    Instead of hardcoding values like region, instance type,
    environment name, etc., we define variables and pass
    values from external files.

    This helps use the same Terraform code for multiple
    environments (dev, staging, production).


--------------------------------------------------
DECLARING A VARIABLE
--------------------------------------------------

Example:

    variable "region" {
        description = "AWS region"
        type        = string
    }

Using the variable:

    provider "aws" {
        region = var.region
    }

Here:
    var.region means the value will come from
    a variable file.


--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS terraform.tfvars ?
--------------------------------------------------

    terraform.tfvars is the default variable file
    used by Terraform.

    Terraform automatically loads this file.

Example:

    region        = "ap-south-1"
    instance_type = "t2.micro"
    environment   = "dev"

When we run:

    terraform plan
    terraform apply

Terraform automatically reads terraform.tfvars.


--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS sbx.tfvars ?
--------------------------------------------------

    sbx.tfvars is a custom variable file.

    It is often used for specific environments.

Example environments:

    dev.tfvars
    qa.tfvars
    prod.tfvars
    sbx.tfvars (sandbox environment)

Example:

    region        = "ap-south-1"
    instance_type = "t3.micro"
    environment   = "sandbox"


--------------------------------------------------
HOW TO USE CUSTOM tfvars FILE
--------------------------------------------------

Command:

    terraform plan -var-file="sbx.tfvars"

or

    terraform apply -var-file="sbx.tfvars"

Terraform will load values from that file.


--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS vars.yaml ?
--------------------------------------------------

    vars.yaml is a YAML formatted variable file.

    YAML files are sometimes used in automation
    pipelines or DevOps workflows.

Example vars.yaml:

    region: ap-south-1
    instance_type: t2.micro
    environment: dev

Terraform itself does not automatically read YAML
files directly unless a script or tool converts them.


--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS provider.yaml ?
--------------------------------------------------

    provider.yaml is not a standard Terraform file.

    It may be used in automation systems or pipelines
    to store provider configuration information.

Example provider.yaml:

    provider:
      aws:
        region: ap-south-1
        profile: dev-account

Usually Terraform provider configuration is written
inside .tf files instead.


--------------------------------------------------
REAL DEVOPS PROJECT STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------

Example Terraform project:

    terraform-project/

        main.tf
        variables.tf
        provider.tf

        terraform.tfvars
        dev.tfvars
        prod.tfvars
        sbx.tfvars


--------------------------------------------------
WORKFLOW EXAMPLE
--------------------------------------------------

1) Write Terraform code

2) Initialize project

    terraform init

3) Run with sandbox variables

    terraform plan -var-file="sbx.tfvars"

4) Apply infrastructure

    terraform apply -var-file="sbx.tfvars"


--------------------------------------------------
SIMPLE SUMMARY
--------------------------------------------------

    Terraform Variables
        Make code reusable.

    terraform.tfvars
        Default variable file.

    sbx.tfvars
        Custom environment variable file.

    vars.yaml
        YAML formatted variables (used in automation).

    provider.yaml
        Not standard Terraform file (pipeline usage).

    Best Practice:
        Use different tfvars files for different
        environments.



