====================================================================
TERRAFORM WORKSPACES
====================================================================

--------------------------------------------------
WHAT ARE TERRAFORM WORKSPACES?
--------------------------------------------------

    Workspaces allow you to manage multiple environments
    (like dev, test, prod) using the SAME Terraform code.

    Each workspace has its own separate state file.

    Default workspace:
        default


--------------------------------------------------
WHY DO WE NEED WORKSPACES?
--------------------------------------------------

    Without workspaces:
        You need separate folders or code copies.

    With workspaces:
        • Same code
        • Different environments
        • Separate state files

    Example:
        dev → small instance
        prod → large instance


--------------------------------------------------
HOW WORKSPACES WORK
--------------------------------------------------

    Terraform stores a separate state file
    for each workspace.

    Example:

        default workspace → terraform.tfstate
        dev workspace     → terraform.tfstate (dev)
        prod workspace    → terraform.tfstate (prod)


--------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT COMMANDS
--------------------------------------------------

    List workspaces:

        terraform workspace list

    Create new workspace:

        terraform workspace new dev

    Switch workspace:

        terraform workspace select dev

    Show current workspace:

        terraform workspace show

    Delete workspace:

        terraform workspace delete dev





--------------------------------------------------
REAL-TIME DEVOPS USE CASE
--------------------------------------------------

    Scenario:
        You have 3 environments:

            dev
            qa
            prod

    Steps:

        terraform workspace new dev
        terraform workspace new qa
        terraform workspace new prod

        terraform workspace select dev
        terraform apply

        terraform workspace select prod
        terraform apply

    Result:

        Same code → Different environments


--------------------------------------------------
WORKSPACES VS tfvars (IMPORTANT)
--------------------------------------------------

    Workspaces:
        • Separate state files
        • Same code

    tfvars:
        • Different input values
        • Same or different environments

Best Practice:

    Use both together:
        workspace + tfvars


--------------------------------------------------
WHEN TO USE WORKSPACES?
--------------------------------------------------

    • Small to medium projects
    • Multiple environments (dev/test/prod)
    • Same infrastructure pattern

Avoid for:

    • Very complex architectures
    • Large enterprise setups
    (use separate backends instead)


--------------------------------------------------
SIMPLE SUMMARY
--------------------------------------------------

    Workspace = Separate environment with its own state

    Commands:

        list    → terraform workspace list
        create  → terraform workspace new dev
        switch  → terraform workspace select dev

    DevOps usage: Simple 

        One code → multiple statefile -->  multiple environments
		
		
