====================================================================
TERRAFORM MODULES – CODE REUSABILITY (FOCUS)
====================================================================

--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS A MODULE (IN SIMPLE TERMS)?
--------------------------------------------------

    A module is a reusable block of Terraform code.

    Instead of writing the same resource code
    again and again, we write it once
    and reuse it multiple times.

DRY - DO NOT REPEAT YOURSELF 

--------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM WITHOUT MODULES
--------------------------------------------------

    Suppose you need:

        • 3 EC2 instances
        • 5 EC2 instances
        • 10 EC2 instances

    Without module:

        You write same EC2 code multiple times ❌

    Issues:

        • Repeated code
        • Hard to update
        • Error-prone


--------------------------------------------------
SOLUTION WITH MODULES
--------------------------------------------------

    Create ONE EC2 module

    Reuse it multiple times with different inputs ✅


--------------------------------------------------
STEP 1: CREATE MODULE
--------------------------------------------------

Folder structure:

    modules/
        ec2/
            main.tf
            variables.tf

--------------------------------------------------
modules/ec2/main.tf
--------------------------------------------------

    resource "aws_instance" "example" {
        ami           = var.ami
        instance_type = var.instance_type
    }


--------------------------------------------------
modules/ec2/variables.tf
--------------------------------------------------

    variable "ami" {}
    variable "instance_type" {}


--------------------------------------------------
STEP 2: USE MODULE MULTIPLE TIMES
--------------------------------------------------

main.tf (root module):

    module "web_server" {
        source         = "./modules/ec2"
        ami            = "ami-123"
        instance_type  = "t2.micro"
    }

    module "app_server" {
        source         = "./modules/ec2"
        ami            = "ami-456"
        instance_type  = "t3.medium"
    }

    module "db_server" {
        source         = "./modules/ec2"
        ami            = "ami-789"
        instance_type  = "t3.large"
    }


--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS HAPPENING HERE?
--------------------------------------------------

    Same EC2 code reused 3 times

    Only inputs changed:

        • web → small instance
        • app → medium instance
        • db  → large instance




--------------------------------------------------
REAL EXAMPLE
--------------------------------------------------

    Security Group Module:

        One module defines:
            - SSH access
            - HTTP access

    Use it for:

        • EC2
        • ALB
        • Bastion host

    Same code reused everywhere


--------------------------------------------------
BENEFITS OF MODULES (REUSABILITY)
--------------------------------------------------

    • Write once, use many times
    • Reduce code duplication
    • Easy to maintain
    • Easy to update

    Example:

        Change in module → affects all usages


--------------------------------------------------
 SUMMARY
--------------------------------------------------

    Module = Reusable code block

    Purpose:
        Avoid repeating Terraform code

    Key idea:

        Write once → Use many times

