====================================================================
TERRAFORM REMOTE BACKEND (S3 – LATEST WITH NATIVE LOCKING)
====================================================================

--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS TERRAFORM BACKEND?
--------------------------------------------------

    Backend defines where Terraform stores
    its state file (terraform.tfstate).

    Default:
        Local file (not safe for teams)

    Remote Backend:
        Stores state in remote location like:
            • S3
            • Terraform Cloud
            • Azure blob Storage
			. Gcs (goolge cloud storage) 


--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS REMOTE BACKEND?
--------------------------------------------------

    Remote backend stores Terraform state
    in a shared location.

    Benefits:

        • Team collaboration
        • Centralized state
        • Backup & versioning
        • Secure access


--------------------------------------------------
WHY REMOTE BACKEND IS REQUIRED?
--------------------------------------------------

    Problems with local state:

        • No sharing
        • Risk of deletion
        • No locking
        • Conflicts in team

    Remote backend solves:

        • Shared access
        • Safe updates
        • Locking mechanism


--------------------------------------------------
STATE LOCKING (IMPORTANT)
--------------------------------------------------

    State locking prevents multiple users
    from modifying infrastructure at same time.

    Example:

        User1 → terraform apply
        User2 → blocked until User1 finishes


--------------------------------------------------
OLD APPROACH (DEPRECATED)
--------------------------------------------------

    S3 + DynamoDB

    S3:
        Stores state file

    DynamoDB:
        Handles locking

Example (OLD):

    terraform {
      backend "s3" {
